= The box model defines how elements are displayed on a webpage and how they
  are displayed.
= The box model can have contents, a border and space inside and outside of it.


                    .-------------------.--.
                    |----------width----|--|
                    |                   |  |
                    |                   |  |
                    |           height  |  |
                    |                   |  |
                    | CONTENT           |  |
                    |.------------------|-.|


= Content can be text, images, or a table, a video, and so on.

                      
            .--------.----------------------------.
            |                                     |
            |                                     |
            |       .V------------------o--.      |
            |       |<---------width----Y->|      |
            |       |                   |  |      |
            |       |                   |  |      |
            |       |               height |      |
            |       |                   |  |      |
            |       | CONTENT           Y  |      |
            |       |.------------------|-.|      |
            |                                     |
            |                             BORDER  |
            |.-----------------------------------.|

= Border: A line around the element, still inside of the element.


            .--------.----------------------------.
            |        |                            |
            |      PADDING                        |
            |        |                            |
            |       .V------------------o--.      |
            |       |<---------width----Y->|      |
            |       |                   |  |      |
            |       |                   |  |      |
            |       |               height |      |
            |       |                   |  |      |
            |       | CONTENT           Y  |      |
            |       |.------------------|-.|      |
            |                                     |
            |                                     |
            |                             BORDER  |
            |.-----------------------------------.|

= Padding is basically invisible white space that we can create around the elements content(inside element).
  = between the content and the border


     ______________________________________._____________
    /                                      |             \
    |                                    MARGIN          |
    |                                      |             |
    |       .--------.---------------------V------.      |
    |       |        |                            |      |
    |       |      PADDING                        |      |
    |       |        |                            |      |
    |       |       .V------------------o--.      |      |
    |       |       |<---------width----Y->|      |      |
    |       |       |                   |  |      |      |
    |       |       |                   |  |      |      |
    |       |       |               height |      |      |
    |       |       |                   |  |      |      |
    |       |       | CONTENT           Y  |      |      |
    |       |       |.------------------|-.|      |      |
    |       |                                     |      |
    |       |                                     |      |
    |       | FILL AREA                        BORDER    |
    |       |.-----------------------------------.|      |
    |                                                    |
    |                                                    |
    |                                                    |
    \____________________________________________________/

= Margin creates empty space around the elements(outside of element)
= In practice, we use margin to create space between elements on our page.
= FILL AREA is area that gets filled with background-color or background-images
= The element occupies the content to the border.
  = The margin itself is outside of the element.


